Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 704
An Act to Clarify Performance Standards for Quarries
Received by the Clerk of the House on February 20, 2025. Referred to the Committee on
Environment and Natural Resources pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered printed pursuant
to Joint Rule 401.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative PLUECKER of Warren.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 38 MRSA §490-X, first ¶, as amended by PL 2007, c. 297, §8, is further
3 amended to read:
4 This article applies to any quarry, including reclaimed and unreclaimed areas, if the
5 quarry is more than one acre in size, the total excavated area including adjacent parcels
6 under a common owner or operator is more than one acre in size or underground production
7 blasting is proposed.
8 Sec. 2. 38 MRSA §490-X, 3rd ¶, as enacted by PL 1995, c. 700, §35, is amended
9 to read:
10 This article does not apply to an excavation or grading preliminary to a construction
11 project, unless blasting is proposed or unless intended to circumvent this article.
12 SUMMARY
1133 This bill amends the performance standards for quarries to apply to any quarry where
1144 blasting is proposed.
Page 1 - 132LR2248(01)
